---
title: Cashew Chicken Stir-Fry with Baby Bok Choy, Carrots, and Jasmine Rice
description: Forget takeout: the path to a savory, Asian-inspired dinner is as simple as breaking out a pan and stir-frying up a storm. This recipe starts with chopping up some bok choy, carrots, and fragrant aromatics. Then, you’ll shift gears for a bit to focus on steaming the rice and toasting the nutty cashews. Afterwards, it all comes back to tossing around those veggies in a pan, followed by pieces of chicken and a savory sweet sauce. The results? A symphony of flavors.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cashew-chicken-stir-fry-c83dc07e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cashew-chicken-stir-fry-5b9bd8deae08b529e730be22-28ee325b.pdf
time required: 25 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cashew-chicken-stir-fry-5b9bd8deae08b529e730be22
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
