Wash and dry all produce. Peel @ginger{1%thumb}, then mince or finely grate. Trim and
discard bottom root ends from @baby bok choy{1}, then separate stalks. Peel
@carrots{2} and slice very thinly on a diagonal. Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry
with a #paper towel{} and place in a #medium bowl{}. Add @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.

Bring 1 cup water and a pinch of salt to a boil in a #small lidded pot{}. Once boiling,
add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and stir. Lower heat, reduce to a gentle simmer, and cover.
Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, until
meal is ready.

Put @cashews{1%ounce} in a #large pan{} and place over medium-high heat. Toast, tossing
often, until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan, then add
@sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Return to medium-high heat and toast seeds, stirring
often, until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to another plate. Wipe out pan again.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in same large pan over medium-high
heat. Add carrots and 2 TBSP water. Cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add bok choy and
cook, tossing, until just tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper and
transfer to another #dish{}. Wipe out pan and heat another drizzle of oil in it over
medium-high heat.

> TIP: Add a splash more water to speed up cooking.

Add chicken to same pan and cook, tossing occasionally, until no longer pink,
~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Add to dish with veggies. Reduce heat
under pan to medium low, then add ginger and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook until fragrant,
about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @honey{1/2%ounce}, 1/2 cup water,
and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a
simmer. Cook until thickened, about ~{3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add veggies, chicken, and half the cashews to same pan and toss to coat with sauce.
Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then stir in half the sesame seeds. Season with salt and
pepper. Divide rice between plates with chicken stirfry to the side. Spoon any
remaining sauce in pan over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining sesame seeds and cashews.